✨ WEDDING SEASON ALERT ✨

As a celebrity stylist who's dressed A-listers for their biggest moments, I'm spilling the tea on how to shop for AND style your perfect Indian wedding lehenga 💃

THE BELLY POUCH HACK THAT CHANGES EVERYTHING:
Wear your lehenga at the NARROWEST part of your waist - not where you think your waist should be! This instantly creates that coveted hourglass silhouette and makes you look snatched in every photo 📸

MY LEHENGA SHOPPING SECRETS:

🛍️ TIMING IS EVERYTHING - Start shopping 3-4 months before wedding season. The good pieces go fast!

🎨 COLOR PSYCHOLOGY - Jewel tones (emerald, ruby, sapphire) photograph beautifully and work on MOST INDIAN skin tone

✂️ FIT OVER EVERYTHING - A well-fitted ₹15,000 lehenga will always look better than a poorly fitted ₹50,000 one..

🪞 THE MIRROR TEST - If you don't feel like a queen in the trial room, keep looking. Your lehenga should make you feel unstoppable!

BRIDAL STYLING INSIDER TIPS:

For brides-to-be: Your lehenga should complement your mehendi, not compete with it. Think of yourself as a complete canvas - every element should work together to create magic ✨

For wedding GUESTS: Respect the bride's color palette but don't fade into the background. You're there to celebrate AND serve looks!

Planning your wedding look or shopping for the season? Drop your questions below - I'm here to help you slay! 👇

Need personalized styling? DM me or link in bio for bridal consultations 💕
